As many as five scientists working in different disciplines have been selected for this yearâ€™s Kerala State Young Scientist Award in recognition of their outstanding contribution to science and technology.The award instituted by the Kerala State Council for Science, Technology and Environment (KSCSTE) carries a grant of Rs.50,000, a start-up research grant, and travel support for a visit abroad for presenting the research work at a conference.WinnersThe award winners include R. Jayakrishnan, Assistant Professor, Department of Physics, Christian College, Chengannur; Bibin John, Scientist, Advanced Energy Systems, VSSC; R.S. Swathi, Assistant Professor, School of Chemistry, IISER, Thiruvananthapuram; E.P. Sreedevi, Assistant Professor, Department of Statistics, Carmel College, Mala; and P. Jayamurthy, Scientist, Agroprocessing and Natural Products division, CSIR-NIIST, Thiruvananthapuram.The award will be given away by Chief Minister Oommen Chandy at the inaugural session of the 28{+t}{+h}Kerala Science Congress at the University of Calicut on January 28.